Speaker 2: Hang on. Hold on a second. Let me take your speaker.

Speaker 1: So I didn't realize when I got my first subscription that I was put on recurring,

Speaker 1: but I want to know how I can get myself taken off this recurring subscription.

Speaker 2: Okay. I can help you with that. Am I speaking to Gary?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Okay, Gary. Give me one second. Let me pull you up.

Speaker 1: than anything else I've tried.

Speaker 1: I don't know. I don't even know if I really need them.

Speaker 2: Let me tell you what individuals do.

Speaker 2: they'll just cut it in half, and that's like bang for their buck.

Speaker 1: So what I'm going to do for you, Gary,

Speaker 2: I'm going to send you out something for free just for you to try.

Speaker 1: I'm not going to charge you.

Speaker 2: I'm going to send you 10 of the 100 mg of the new and improved Viagra.

Speaker 1: That's the one that really works really good,

Speaker 2: and the 100 mg is going to be so much better than the 50 mg.

Speaker 1: Let me tell you the difference of these.

Speaker 2: It's going to be a white-shaped diamond pill,

Speaker 1: but it's going to have the number 100 on the back.

Speaker 2: I'm not going to put you on a monthly refill like this.

Speaker 1: No, no, bear with me.

Speaker 2: Listen to what I'm saying.

Speaker 1: I want you to try these.

Speaker 2: I'm going to put a pause to everything on your account,

Speaker 1: but I want to keep your prescription out there because I'm going to change it

Speaker 2: to what I'm sending you now.

Speaker 1: So whenever you want to order, you can order,

Speaker 2: and you'll get the ones I'm going to send you now.

Speaker 1: So I'm not going to have them come to you every month automatically.

Speaker 2: I'm going to postpone any order for like four months, as far as that's concerned,

Speaker 1: to make sure that you have a chance to try these.

Speaker 2: I guarantee you when you try these, you'll see a drastic difference.

Speaker 1: With these, you're not going to have the same side effects that some people get,

Speaker 2: like the dizziness and the headaches, and that's their stomachs.

Speaker 1: They also work faster.

Speaker 2: They're going to last longer, and you're going to see a drastic difference with these.

Speaker 1: I couldn't swore that's what I ordered.

Speaker 2: I did it on my phone, and, of course,

Speaker 1: the screen is not as big as a computer screen or an iPad.

Speaker 2: But I could have swore that this was supposed to only take 15 minutes to take effect.

Speaker 1: No, you don't have those.

Speaker 2: You don't have those.

Speaker 1: That's what I'm saying.

Speaker 2: That's why I want to send you out the latest.

Speaker 1: Yeah, that's what I thought I ordered.

Speaker 1: That's why you're saying what you're saying.

Speaker 1: Okay?

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Anytime.

Speaker 2: I tried them.

Speaker 1: I didn't like them.

Speaker 2: I want to cancel.

Speaker 1: That's what's going to happen.

Speaker 2: But trust me.

Speaker 1: You'll see what I'm talking about when you try these.

Speaker 1: or whatever it's called.

Speaker 2: Well, no.

Speaker 1: It's just new and improved.

Speaker 2: The Pfizer labs in France have made a better, new, and improved pill.

Speaker 1: It's going to have the same – your label is going to say the same,

Speaker 2: but only this is going to be 100 milligrams.

Speaker 1: And like I said, if it's too strong, just break it in half.

Speaker 2: But I'm telling you, it's going to work for you like you'd be surprised.

Speaker 1: You're not going to have those same effects that a lot of people get,

Speaker 2: like the dizziness and the headaches and the stomach aches.

Speaker 1: I have gotten headaches with these other ones.

Speaker 2: That's what I'm trying to tell you.

Speaker 1: You're not going to have that.

Speaker 2: You're going to see a drastic difference with these.

Speaker 1: Okay?

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: And it's going to be – you said it'll be four months now?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I'm going to hold off for four months,

Speaker 1: but you can always call and order before then, which I know you probably will.

Speaker 2: That's not a problem.

Speaker 1: And I'm keeping you at the discounted price, too, when you do order.

Speaker 2: You're not going to be upgraded,

Speaker 1: because I know they're going to go up on the prices real soon,

Speaker 2: because a lot of stuff comes from the labs in France.

Speaker 1: Anybody that's not on a prescription already,

Speaker 2: they're going to have to pay for that tear.

Speaker 1: So that's another advantage of keeping your prescription active.

Speaker 2: Okay?

Speaker 1: You said it better.

Speaker 2: I'll try it.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: Like I said, and if you don't like it, just give us a call like you do now,

Speaker 1: and you won't get anything after that going forward.

Speaker 2: That's what you want.

Speaker 1: But I guarantee you're going to really, really appreciate it.

Speaker 2: These are the best that's out there, man.

Speaker 1: Trust me on that.

Speaker 2: And they'll have the 100 rate going, right?

Speaker 1: They're going to have the 100, and that's how you can see the difference.

Speaker 2: There's going to be a white-shaped diamond pill with the number 100.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: Okay?

Speaker 1: That's what I got.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: The next one that you're shipping out, let me try them.

Speaker 1: And I'm still getting the shipment that I got an email for the other day.

Speaker 2: Exactly.

Speaker 1: So mine is going to be after that.

Speaker 2: But mine is going to have the 100 on it.

Speaker 1: That's the one you're going to look for.

Speaker 2: And there's no charge for you on that one.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: I'll give it a shot.

Speaker 2: And my name is Jimmy.

Speaker 1: Give me a call back when you're ready to reorder, because I know you're going to want to reorder these.

Speaker 2: All right?

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: All right, Jimmy.

Speaker 2: Thanks.

Speaker 1: Take care.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.

Speaker 1: All right.
